people.name: Christian Bakkerud
people.aboutText: Ryo Nishikido (錦戸 亮, Nishikido Ryō, born November 3, 1984) is a Japanese idol, singer, actor and songwriter. He is a member of Japanese boy band Kanjani Eight and was also a member of Japanese male idol group News, both of which are under the management of Johnny & Associates.

people.name: Ryo Nishikido
people.aboutText: Christian Bakkerud (3 November 1984 – 11 September 2011) was a Danish racing driver, who competed in the 2007 and 2008 GP2 Series seasons, albeit hindered by a recurrent back injury.

people.name: LaMarr Woodley
people.aboutText: LaMarr Dudley Woodley (born November 3, 1984) is an American football outside linebacker for the Arizona Cardinals of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Michigan, where he was recognized as a unanimous All-American, and was drafted by the Pittsburgh Steelers in the second round of the 2007 NFL Draft.

people.name: Mina Fukui
people.aboutText: Mina Fukui (福井 未菜, Fukui Mina, November 3, 1984) is a Japanese actress, tarento and gravure model from Nabari, Mie Prefecture.

people.name: Tyler Hansbrough
people.aboutText: Andrew Tyler Hansbrough (born November 3, 1985) is an American professional basketball player for the Charlotte Hornets of the National Basketball Association (NBA). Hansbrough played college basketball for the North Carolina Tar Heels men's basketball team where he was a unanimous selection for the 2006, 2007, 2008 and 2009 Atlantic Coast Conference All Conference Team, 2006 ACC Freshman of the Year, and 2008 ACC Player of the Year. He is the ACC's all-time leading scorer, and he won the Wooden Award and earned National Player of the Year honors in 2008.

people.name: Philipp Tschauner
people.aboutText: Philipp Tschauner (born 3 November 1985) is a German professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Hannover 96 in the Bundesliga. During his career, he has played for 1. FC Nürnberg, 1860 Munich, and FC St.

people.name: Paul Derbyshire
people.aboutText: Paul Derbyshire (born 3 November 1986) is an Italian rugby union player. Derbyshire, who is a flanker, plays club rugby for Benetton Treviso. He made his debut for Italy against Australia on 13 June 2009.

people.name: Jermaine Jones
people.aboutText:
Jermaine Jones (born November 3, 1986) is an American singer and actor from Pine Hill, New Jersey, who came in twelfth place after being disqualified from the eleventh season of American Idol.
^ a b c "Jermaine Jones of 'American Idol' does talk to his father, says his mother". March 8, 2012.

people.name: Beth Kingston
people.aboutText: Jasmine Trias (born November 3, 1986) is an American singer-entertainer who was the third place finalist on the third season of American Idol.

people.name: Jasmine Trias
people.aboutText: Beth Kingston (born 3 November 1986)  is an English actress best known for playing India Longford in the British soap opera Hollyoaks.

people.name: Piet Velthuizen
people.aboutText: Piet Velthuizen (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈpit ˈvɛlt.ˌɦœy̯.zə(n)]) (born 3 November 1986 in Nijmegen, Gelderland), is a Dutch goalkeeper who currently plays for Vitesse. He has participated in the 2008 Summer Olympics.

people.name: Heo Young-saeng
people.aboutText:
Heo Young-Saeng (Hangul: 허영생; hanja: 許永生; born: November 3, 1986) is a South Korean entertainer and the lead singer and the main vocalist of boyband SS501.
In 2010, Heo left DSP Media, who managed him as part of SS501, and moved to B2M Entertainment, with bandmate Kim Kyu-Jong, to pursue his solo career. His debut album as a soloist entitled Let It Go was released in May 2011.

people.name: Cameron
people.aboutText: Colin Rand Kaepernick (born November 3, 1987) is an American football quarterback for the San Francisco 49ers of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Nevada, and was drafted by the 49ers in the second round of the 2011 NFL Draft. At Nevada, he twice was named the Western Athletic Offensive Player of the Year, and he was the Most Valuable Player of the 2008 Humanitarian Bowl.

people.name: Colin Kaepernick
people.aboutText:
Ariane Nicole Andrew (born November 3, 1987) is an American singer, model, dancer, valet and professional wrestler currently signed to World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) under the ring name Cameron.
Under her real name, Andrew joined the 2011 season of Tough Enough where she was the first competitor eliminated. She later signed with WWE and joined Naomi in forming The Funkadactyls.

people.name: Ty Lawson
people.aboutText: Felix Schütz (born November 3, 1987) is a German professional ice hockey player for Dinamo Riga of the KHL. He was drafted by the Buffalo Sabres in 2006

people.name: Felix Schütz
people.aboutText: Tywon Ronell "Ty" Lawson (born November 3, 1987) is an American professional basketball player for the Houston Rockets of the National Basketball Association (NBA). Lawson played college basketball for North Carolina where he won a national championship his junior year. He was drafted with the 18th overall pick in the 2009 NBA draft by the Minnesota Timberwolves and was immediately traded to the Denver Nuggets for a future first round pick.

people.name: Gemma Ward
people.aboutText: Gemma Louise Ward (born 3 November 1987) is an Australian fashion model turned actress. Born in Perth, Western Australia, Ward was first scouted at the age of 14, and made her Australian Fashion Week debut aged 15. She later became the youngest model to appear on the cover of the American edition of Vogue, later appearing on the covers of both Teen Vogue and Time.

people.name: Angus McLaren
people.aboutText: Angus McLaren (born 3 November 1988) is an Australian actor who is best known for his roles in the television series Packed to the Rafters as Nathan Rafter and H2O: Just Add Water as Lewis McCartney.

people.name: Paula DeAnda
people.aboutText: Paula Dacia DeAnda (born November 3, 1989) is an Mexican American pop singer-songwriter and actress. She first came to prominence with her first single, "Doing Too Much", which became a hit in the Southwest. She then got the opportunity to audition for Clive Davis, who signed her to Arista Records on the spot.

people.name: Joyce Jonathan
people.aboutText:
Joyce Jonathan (born 3 November 1989 in Levallois-Perret) is a French singer and songwriter.
Her first album Sur mes gardes went gold in May 2010 only five months after its release. Less than a year after, the album was certified platinum.

people.name: Ellyse Perry
people.aboutText: Ellyse Alexandra Perry (born 3 November 1990) is an Australian sportswoman who made her debut for both the Australian cricket and the Australian women's national soccer team at the age of 16. She played her first cricket international in July 2007 before earning her first football cap for Australia a month later. Perry is the youngest person to represent Australia in cricket and the first Australian to have appeared in both cricket and association football World Cups.

people.name: Valeria Solovyeva
people.aboutText:
Valeria Alexandrovna Solovyeva (Russian: Валерия Александровна Соловьёва; born 3 November 1992 in Saratov) is a Russian tennis player.
Solovyeva has won two doubles titles on the WTA tour, as well as one singles and nine doubles titles on the ITF circuit in her career. On 27 May 2013, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 163.

people.name: Kendall Jenner
people.aboutText: Kendall Nicole Jenner (born November 3, 1995) is an American fashion model and television personality. Jenner first came to public attention for appearing in the E! reality television show Keeping Up with the Kardashians.
